               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipits and headings of the texts; numbers and titles of the chapters and the word mǝˤǝraf; numbers of the “tituli”; parts of the Canon tables; elements of the punctuation signs and the Ethiopic numerals; names of the donors and the scribes; letters ወ and ደ in the genealogy of Christ (fols. 112vb-113vb).&#xD;
&#xD;
On the incipit pages of Mäqdǝmä wängel and of each Gospel, a few lines are rubricated (in groups of two lines, alternating with black lines).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>In the “tituli” for the Gospel of John there is a mistake in chapter numbering: no. 10 is followed by no. 20, so that the total number of the chapters as written by the scribe is 29.</note>
                     <note>For details concerning the traditional introduction texts s. R.W. COWLEY, "New Testament Introduction in the Andemta Commentary Tradition", Ostkirchliche Studien 26, 1977, 144-92 ; R. ZUURMOND, Novum Testamentum Aethiopice: the Synoptic Gospels, Part I: General Introduction, Part II: Edition of the Gospel of Mark, Stuttgart, 1989 (AeF 27), 6-36.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The "Golden Gospel" of Maryam Mäkan church.</note>
                  </msItem>
