                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#193ra">Fol. 193ra</locus>: Ownership note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 193ra: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ {ዘደብረማርያም። መካ [sic]} ዘመጽአ፡ እምሀገረ፡ {መካን፡} ምስለ፡ አቡነ፡ መዝገበ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ወዘአውፅኦ፡ እምዝንቱ፡ ደብር፡ ዘሀገረ፡ {ማርያም፡} ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 193ra: This (is the) book of Däbrä Maryam Mäka(n) which came from the country of Kaswa with ʾabunä Mäzgäbä Śǝllase. He who steals it or erases (its text) or takes it out of this church of the country of Maryam shall be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul.</q>
                           Written in red ink; the hand appears to be the same as the one that executed rubrication. One name is washed out. 
The names connected with the church of Mäkan Maryam were added in pencil later, replacing the name ካስዋ፡ (an alternative appellation of the monastery of Gundä Gunde) written originally. By substituting the name of Kaswa with the name of Mäkan the scribe created a contradiction in the note.
ʾAbunä Mäzgäbä Śǝllase was the abbot of Gundä Gunde monastery in the second half of the 17th – beginning of the 18th cent.
                        </item>
